Anonymous Thu 26 Aug 2021 23:05:49 No.41190865 Report

>>41184121
A lot of anthros would loose much of the advantages enjoyed by the animals they're based on just by being scaled up to relative size. The square-cube law means bugs can't be scaled up very much without self-destructing. A lot of anthros would not have the same relative strength due to their increased mass, and their increased mass would also drastically affect their ability to cool themselves off with a thick fur coat and no ability to sweat. (Alternatively, a horse scaled down to human-size is also not going to have the same absolute speed.) So although some anthros would probably still be significantly better (and worse) at some kinds of sports than others, their advantages would be a hell of a lot more modest than it might initially seem.

Probably there'd just be some kind of extension of the way many sports already have male and female teams, possibly by integrating certain anthros into those teams (irrespective of the anthros' sex) based on their "base" abilities at that particular sport. Which, obviously, can be a writing prompt for someone whose brain hasn't burnt out like mine. Maybe there'd be a few other leagues for anthros with exceptional abilities, too. Amateur sportsball-playing by ordinary people (of whatever species) probably wouldn't be affected too much.
